STP Versions

### IEEE Open Standards

- 802.1D Spanning Tree Protocol (STP): Original STP, uses one spanning tree for all VLANs in the LAN
- 802.1w Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol (RSTP): Improved convergence time, uses one spanning tree for all VLANs in the LAN
- 802.1s Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol (MSTP): Enables mapping VLANs in to different spanning trees for load balancing, VLANs can be grouped in to seperate STP
                                                 instances

### Cisco Proprietary

- Per VLAN Spanning Tree Plus (PVST+): ENhancement to 802.1D, seperate STP instance for each VLAN, default on Cisco switches
- Rapid Per VLAN Spanning Tree PLus (RPVST+): Enhancement to 802.1w, Improved convergence time over PVST+, seperate STP instance for every VLAN, VLANs cannot be
                                              grouped in to seperate STP instances
                                              
